<taxonomicName authority="(Dlabola, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[350,756,1900,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis box="[350,584,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Lethierium cedricolum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J." box="[599,749,1900,1924]" pageId="13" pageNumber="530" pagination="21 - 59" refId="ref8826" refString="Dlabola, J. (1989) Neue Issiden und andere Zikadenarten des Mediterraneums und vom zuliegenden Eremial (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45 B (1), 21 - 59." type="journal article" year="1989">Dlabola, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, male, Timhadit. 39—face; 40—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="14" pageNumber="531" startId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" targetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1513,1609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1513,1537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">FIGURES 41–46.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Dlabola, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[348,750,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis box="[348,580,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">Lethierium cedricolum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J." box="[594,743,1513,1537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531" pagination="21 - 59" refId="ref8826" refString="Dlabola, J. (1989) Neue Issiden und andere Zikadenarten des Mediterraneums und vom zuliegenden Eremial (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45 B (1), 21 - 59." type="journal article" year="1989">Dlabola, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1691,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1691,1717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">Coloration.</emphasis>
General coloration straw yellow, with light brown to dark brown spots on clavus and dark brown dots on corium medially and in the cells of membrane. Metope with dark brown traces of larval sensory pits. Pedicel light yellow to light brown, with light sensory organs. Second segment of rostrum brown, third one dark brown to black apically. Flagellum black. Apices of leg spines black. Claws dark brown. Abdominal sternites IV–VI straw yellow, with dark brown to black areas surrounding sensory pits. Abdominal tergites straw yellow to dark brown, with light yellow median line. Gonoplacs dark brown, each with large light yellow lateral spot. Female anal tube straw yellow to light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1691,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,528,1943,1969]" pageId="14" pageNumber="531">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[384,515,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="14" pageNumber="531">Figs 47–52</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Anal tube elongate, slightly narrowing basally and apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="14" pageNumber="531">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
), with a rounded process on each its lateral margin (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[952,1036,1979,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="14" pageNumber="531">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Anal column short and wide, ¹⁄
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="15" pageNumber="532" startId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" targetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1887,1983]" pageId="15" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1887,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="532">FIGURES 47–52.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[347,595,1887,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandilobum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[347,595,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="532">Lethierium grandilobum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[602,683,1887,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[602,683,1887,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="16" pageNumber="533" startId="16.[151,264,1566,1590]" targetBox="[161,1429,191,1534]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1566,1626]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1566,1590]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">FIGURES 53–55.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[348,559,1566,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[348,559,1566,1590]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Lethierium carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[566,643,1566,1590]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[566,643,1566,1590]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female paratype, Bou Naceur. 53—face; 54—eye, scapus, pedicel, and paranotal lobe, frontal view; 55—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1708,2023]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
of anal tube length. Aedeagus with strongly curved ventral hooks, arising at its middle, thicker in their middle parts. Lobes of phallobase basement massive, enlarged and rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[974,1061,1744,1771]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Ventral phalobase lobe with an apical notch (
<figureCitation box="[303,388,1780,1807]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Style with weakly concave or nearly straight hind margin and widely rounded caudo-dorsal angle (
<figureCitation box="[228,312,1816,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Capitulum of style on long neck, flattened antero-apically, not narrowing apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[159,290,1852,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,188,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@15.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Lethierium grandilobum sp. nov., holotype, male genitalia. 47—anal tube, pygofer, and penis, lateral view; 48—anal tube, dorsal view; 49—penis and connective, lateral view; 50—penis and connective, ventral view; 51—style, lateral view; 52—style, dorsal view. Out of scale." pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Figs 51, 52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1708,2023]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,405,1888,1915]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Hind margin of sternite VII with large semicircular labial process medially as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">L. cedricolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ovipositor structure generally as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bergevin" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[632,750,1925,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperi">
<emphasis box="[632,750,1925,1950]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">L. juniperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Anal tube convex (in lateral view), long, 3.5 times as long as wide medially, narrowing apically, with rounded apex (in dorsal view). Anterior connective lamina of gonapophysis VIII with three teeth in lateral group.
</paragraph>
