<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,330,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">Notes.</emphasis>
The species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dlabola, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[657,1005,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis box="[657,815,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">L. cedricolum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J." box="[831,998,330,356]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534" pagination="21 - 59" refId="ref8826" refString="Dlabola, J. (1989) Neue Issiden und andere Zikadenarten des Mediterraneums und vom zuliegenden Eremial (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45 B (1), 21 - 59." type="journal article" year="1989">Dlabola, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, both species are known from central 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,367,393]" name="Morocco" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, but from different mountain Ranges—High Atlas and Middle Atlas. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola, J." box="[1032,1202,366,392]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534" pagination="21 - 59" refId="ref8826" refString="Dlabola, J. (1989) Neue Issiden und andere Zikadenarten des Mediterraneums und vom zuliegenden Eremial (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45 B (1), 21 - 59." type="journal article" year="1989">Dlabola (1989)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<specimenCount box="[1313,1436,366,393]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
from Asni in the type series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dlabola" authorityYear="1989" box="[506,807,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Hysteropterum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cedricolum">
<emphasis box="[506,807,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">Hysteropterum cedricolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[889,989,403,429]" pageId="17" pageNumber="534">paratype</typeStatus>
. Apparently this female also belongs to the new species described above.
</paragraph>
